headline: How Norwegian's Pioneering Renewable Fuel Deal With Repsol (NCLH) Has Changed Its Investment Story
summary: Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings recently announced an 8-year agreement with Repsol to supply renewable marine fuels, including biofuels and renewable methanol from 2029, for its vessels at the Port of Barcelona starting in the 2026 European season. This partnership marks a cruise industry first, supporting Norwegian’s Sail & Sustain program and advancing its long-term goals to reduce greenhouse gas intensity and achieve net zero emissions by 2050.
